= Topic: People First: The Heart of China's Development

My speech will focus on the idea of "people first", which means that the well-being of the people should always be the center of social development. First, I will explain the meaning of this idea and why it is important in modern China. Second, I will talk about how "people first" can be seen in daily life, such as better education, medical care, cleaner communities, and services for the elderly. Third, I will discuss the role of young people. As students, we should care about others, respect every person, and try to make small changes in our school and society. In conclusion, I will show that "people first" is not only a national idea, but also a guide for our own actions.
